<qti-assessment-item xmlns="http://www.imsglobal.org/xsd/imsqtiasi_v3p0" xmlns:m="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" xmlns:xsi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance" identifier="Q36_v14" title="Q36_v14" time-dependent="false" adaptive="false" xsi:schemaLocation="http://www.imsglobal.org/xsd/imsqtiasi_v3p0 https://purl.imsglobal.org/spec/qti/v3p0/schema/xsd/imsqti_asiv3p0_v1p0.xsd">
  <qti-response-declaration identifier="RESPONSE" cardinality="single" base-type="identifier">
    <qti-correct-response>
      <qti-value>ChoiceA</qti-value>
    </qti-correct-response>
  </qti-response-declaration>
  <qti-outcome-declaration identifier="FEEDBACK" cardinality="single" base-type="identifier"/>
  <qti-outcome-declaration identifier="SOLUTION" cardinality="single" base-type="identifier"/>
  <qti-outcome-declaration identifier="SCORE" cardinality="single" base-type="float"><qti-default-value><qti-value>0</qti-value></qti-default-value></qti-outcome-declaration>
  <qti-item-body>
    <p>Considera el siguiente sistema de ecuaciones:</p>
    <div>
      <m:math display="block">
        <m:mtable>
          <m:mtr>
            <m:mtd>
              <m:mi>x</m:mi>
              <m:mo>+</m:mo>
              <m:mi>y</m:mi>
              <m:mo>=</m:mo>
              <m:mn>5</m:mn>
            </m:mtd>
          </m:mtr>
          <m:mtr>
            <m:mtd>
              <m:mn>2</m:mn>
              <m:mi>x</m:mi>
              <m:mo>−</m:mo>
              <m:mi>y</m:mi>
              <m:mo>=</m:mo>
              <m:mn>7</m:mn>
            </m:mtd>
          </m:mtr>
        </m:mtable>
      </m:math>
    </div>
    <qti-choice-interaction response-identifier="RESPONSE" shuffle="false" max-choices="1">
      <qti-prompt>Respecto de la solución de este sistema, ¿cuál de las siguientes afirmaciones es correcta?</qti-prompt>
      <qti-simple-choice identifier="ChoiceA">La solución es (4, 1).<qti-feedback-inline identifier="FB_ChoiceA" outcome-identifier="FEEDBACK">¡Correcto! Al reemplazar <strong>x = 4</strong> e <strong>y = 1</strong> en el sistema, se obtiene <strong>4 + 1 = 5</strong> y también <strong>2 · 4 − 1 = 8 − 1 = 7</strong>. Por lo tanto, <strong>(4, 1)</strong> satisface ambas ecuaciones.</qti-feedback-inline></qti-simple-choice>
      
      <qti-simple-choice identifier="ChoiceB">La solución es (1, 4).<qti-feedback-inline identifier="FB_ChoiceB" outcome-identifier="FEEDBACK">Incorrecto. Al reemplazar <strong>x = 1</strong> e <strong>y = 4</strong>, la primera ecuación sí se cumple porque <strong>1 + 4 = 5</strong>, pero la segunda no, ya que <strong>2 · 1 − 4 = 2 − 4 = −2</strong> y <strong>−2 ≠ 7</strong>. Entonces <strong>(1, 4)</strong> no es solución del sistema.</qti-feedback-inline></qti-simple-choice>
      
      <qti-simple-choice identifier="ChoiceC">No existe solución para este sistema.<qti-feedback-inline identifier="FB_ChoiceC" outcome-identifier="FEEDBACK">Incorrecto. Sí existe solución. Un contraejemplo concreto es <strong>(4, 1)</strong>, porque al reemplazar se cumple <strong>4 + 1 = 5</strong> y <strong>2 · 4 − 1 = 8 − 1 = 7</strong>. Como existe al menos un par que satisface ambas ecuaciones, la afirmación es falsa.</qti-feedback-inline></qti-simple-choice>
      
      <qti-simple-choice identifier="ChoiceD">El sistema tiene infinitas soluciones.<qti-feedback-inline identifier="FB_ChoiceD" outcome-identifier="FEEDBACK">Incorrecto. Al sumar las ecuaciones del sistema se obtiene una única ecuación para <strong>x</strong>: <strong>(x + y) + (2x − y) = 5 + 7</strong>, es decir, <strong>3x = 12</strong>, por lo que <strong>x = 4</strong>. Luego, al reemplazar en <strong>x + y = 5</strong>, resulta <strong>4 + y = 5</strong> y entonces <strong>y = 1</strong>. Así, el sistema tiene una única solución, no infinitas.</qti-feedback-inline></qti-simple-choice>
    </qti-choice-interaction>
    <qti-feedback-block identifier="show" outcome-identifier="SOLUTION" show-hide="show">
      <qti-content-body>
        <p><strong>Resolución paso a paso del sistema</strong></p>
        <ol>
          <li>
            <p><strong>Paso 1: Escribir el sistema</strong></p>
            <m:math display="block">
              <m:mtable>
                <m:mtr>
                  <m:mtd>
                    <m:mi>x</m:mi>
                    <m:mo>+</m:mo>
                    <m:mi>y</m:mi>
                    <m:mo>=</m:mo>
                    <m:mn>5</m:mn>
                  </m:mtd>
                </m:mtr>
                <m:mtr>
                  <m:mtd>
                    <m:mn>2</m:mn>
                    <m:mi>x</m:mi>
                    <m:mo>−</m:mo>
                    <m:mi>y</m:mi>
                    <m:mo>=</m:mo>
                    <m:mn>7</m:mn>
                  </m:mtd>
                </m:mtr>
              </m:mtable>
            </m:math>
          </li>
          <li>
            <p><strong>Paso 2: Sumar las dos ecuaciones</strong></p>
            <p>Se suman miembro a miembro. Como aparece <m:math><m:mi>y</m:mi></m:math> en una ecuación y <m:math><m:mo>−</m:mo><m:mi>y</m:mi></m:math> en la otra, esas cantidades se eliminan.</p>
            <m:math display="block">
              <m:mrow>
                <m:mo>(</m:mo>
                <m:mi>x</m:mi>
                <m:mo>+</m:mo>
                <m:mi>y</m:mi>
                <m:mo>)</m:mo>
                <m:mo>+</m:mo>
                <m:mo>(</m:mo>
                <m:mn>2</m:mn>
                <m:mi>x</m:mi>
                <m:mo>−</m:mo>
                <m:mi>y</m:mi>
                <m:mo>)</m:mo>
                <m:mo>=</m:mo>
                <m:mn>5</m:mn>
                <m:mo>+</m:mo>
                <m:mn>7</m:mn>
              </m:mrow>
            </m:math>
            <m:math display="block">
              <m:mrow>
                <m:mn>3</m:mn>
                <m:mi>x</m:mi>
                <m:mo>=</m:mo>
                <m:mn>12</m:mn>
              </m:mrow>
            </m:math>
            <m:math display="block">
              <m:mrow>
                <m:mi>x</m:mi>
                <m:mo>=</m:mo>
                <m:mn>4</m:mn>
              </m:mrow>
            </m:math>
          </li>
          <li>
            <p><strong>Paso 3: Reemplazar el valor de x en una ecuación</strong></p>
            <p>Usamos la primera ecuación:</p>
            <m:math display="block">
              <m:mrow>
                <m:mi>x</m:mi>
                <m:mo>+</m:mo>
                <m:mi>y</m:mi>
                <m:mo>=</m:mo>
                <m:mn>5</m:mn>
              </m:mrow>
            </m:math>
            <p>Reemplazando <m:math><m:mi>x</m:mi><m:mo>=</m:mo><m:mn>4</m:mn></m:math>:</p>
            <m:math display="block">
              <m:mrow>
                <m:mn>4</m:mn>
                <m:mo>+</m:mo>
                <m:mi>y</m:mi>
                <m:mo>=</m:mo>
                <m:mn>5</m:mn>
              </m:mrow>
            </m:math>
            <m:math display="block">
              <m:mrow>
                <m:mi>y</m:mi>
                <m:mo>=</m:mo>
                <m:mn>1</m:mn>
              </m:mrow>
            </m:math>
          </li>
          <li>
            <p><strong>Paso 4: Verificar la solución en ambas ecuaciones</strong></p>
            <p>Primera ecuación:</p>
            <m:math display="block">
              <m:mrow>
                <m:mn>4</m:mn>
                <m:mo>+</m:mo>
                <m:mn>1</m:mn>
                <m:mo>=</m:mo>
                <m:mn>5</m:mn>
              </m:mrow>
            </m:math>
            <p>Segunda ecuación:</p>
            <m:math display="block">
              <m:mrow>
                <m:mn>2</m:mn>
                <m:mo>·</m:mo>
                <m:mn>4</m:mn>
                <m:mo>−</m:mo>
                <m:mn>1</m:mn>
                <m:mo>=</m:mo>
                <m:mn>8</m:mn>
                <m:mo>−</m:mo>
                <m:mn>1</m:mn>
                <m:mo>=</m:mo>
                <m:mn>7</m:mn>
              </m:mrow>
            </m:math>
          </li>
          <li>
            <p><strong>Conclusión</strong></p>
            <p>La solución del sistema es <m:math><m:mrow><m:mo>(</m:mo><m:mn>4</m:mn><m:mo>,</m:mo><m:mn>1</m:mn><m:mo>)</m:mo></m:mrow></m:math>. Por lo tanto, la afirmación correcta es <strong>La solución es (4, 1)</strong>.</p>
          </li>
        </ol>
      </qti-content-body>
    </qti-feedback-block>
  </qti-item-body>
  <qti-response-processing>
    <qti-response-condition>
      <qti-response-if>
        <qti-match>
          <qti-variable identifier="RESPONSE"/>
          <qti-base-value base-type="identifier">ChoiceA</qti-base-value>
        </qti-match>
        <qti-set-outcome-value identifier="SCORE">
          <qti-base-value base-type="float">1</qti-base-value>
        </qti-set-outcome-value>
        <qti-set-outcome-value identifier="FEEDBACK">
          <qti-base-value base-type="identifier">FB_ChoiceA</qti-base-value>
        </qti-set-outcome-value>
        <qti-set-outcome-value identifier="SOLUTION">
          <qti-base-value base-type="identifier">show</qti-base-value>
        </qti-set-outcome-value>
      </qti-response-if>
      <qti-response-else-if>
        <qti-match>
          <qti-variable identifier="RESPONSE"/>
          <qti-base-value base-type="identifier">ChoiceB</qti-base-value>
        </qti-match>
        <qti-set-outcome-value identifier="FEEDBACK">
          <qti-base-value base-type="identifier">FB_ChoiceB</qti-base-value>
        </qti-set-outcome-value>
        <qti-set-outcome-value identifier="SOLUTION">
          <qti-base-value base-type="identifier">show</qti-base-value>
        </qti-set-outcome-value>
      </qti-response-else-if>
      <qti-response-else-if>
        <qti-match>
          <qti-variable identifier="RESPONSE"/>
          <qti-base-value base-type="identifier">ChoiceC</qti-base-value>
        </qti-match>
        <qti-set-outcome-value identifier="FEEDBACK">
          <qti-base-value base-type="identifier">FB_ChoiceC</qti-base-value>
        </qti-set-outcome-value>
        <qti-set-outcome-value identifier="SOLUTION">
          <qti-base-value base-type="identifier">show</qti-base-value>
        </qti-set-outcome-value>
      </qti-response-else-if>
      <qti-response-else-if>
        <qti-match>
          <qti-variable identifier="RESPONSE"/>
          <qti-base-value base-type="identifier">ChoiceD</qti-base-value>
        </qti-match>
        <qti-set-outcome-value identifier="FEEDBACK">
          <qti-base-value base-type="identifier">FB_ChoiceD</qti-base-value>
        </qti-set-outcome-value>
        <qti-set-outcome-value identifier="SOLUTION">
          <qti-base-value base-type="identifier">show</qti-base-value>
        </qti-set-outcome-value>
      </qti-response-else-if>
      <qti-response-else>
        <qti-set-outcome-value identifier="FEEDBACK">
          <qti-base-value base-type="identifier">FB_ChoiceB</qti-base-value>
        </qti-set-outcome-value>
        <qti-set-outcome-value identifier="SOLUTION">
          <qti-base-value base-type="identifier">show</qti-base-value>
        </qti-set-outcome-value>
      </qti-response-else>
    </qti-response-condition>
  </qti-response-processing>
</qti-assessment-item>